1
00:00:08,500 --> 00:00:09,625
[MONTMORENCY]
Mercenaries and knights alike,

2
00:00:09,708 --> 00:00:10,875
hear me now!

3
00:00:10,958 --> 00:00:13,708
We ride to Orleans,

4
00:00:13,791 --> 00:00:16,208
where we shall turn
the tide of battle!

5
00:00:16,291 --> 00:00:17,666
[SOLDIERS cheering]

6
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:21,083
[LA TREMOILLE]
I won't let you play the part

7
00:00:21,166 --> 00:00:22,583
of the heroic liberator.

8
00:00:22,666 --> 00:00:24,875
-I'll kill you.
-[ALENCON] Montmorency!

9
00:00:24,958 --> 00:00:26,250
[MONTMORENCY]
Alencon.

10
00:00:26,333 --> 00:00:28,875
[ALENCON] Of course,
and I haven't come alone.

11
00:00:28,958 --> 00:00:30,333
Who are all these people?

12
00:00:30,416 --> 00:00:32,500
[ALENCON] They're my sister's
personal regiment.

13
00:00:32,583 --> 00:00:34,750
All troops, pull back at once.

14
00:00:34,833 --> 00:00:36,583
We need to make
a tactical withdrawal.

15
00:00:36,666 --> 00:00:39,666
[RICHEMONT] Montmorency,
you must fulfill your duty,

16
00:00:39,750 --> 00:00:41,666
only then will you become
a true knight.

17
00:00:41,750 --> 00:00:43,125
[ALENCON]
If Montmorency can reach Jeanne,

18
00:00:43,208 --> 00:00:44,541
then I know we can beat them.

19
00:00:44,625 --> 00:00:46,000
We just have to get him to her.

20
00:00:46,083 --> 00:00:48,291
[MONTMORENCY]
Yeah, let's ride.

21
00:00:48,375 --> 00:00:49,916
[SOLDIERS yelling]

22
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:51,291
[SOLDIER 1]
What do we do, sir?

23
00:00:52,333 --> 00:00:54,208
[SOLDIER 2] Commander Campbell
has fallen, sir!

24
00:00:54,291 --> 00:00:55,791
We've just received a report

25
00:00:55,875 --> 00:00:57,791
that the dark alchemist
has entered the fortress, sir.

26
00:00:57,875 --> 00:00:59,250
What should we do?

27
00:00:59,333 --> 00:01:00,416
[ASTAROTH]
The elixir in her body

28
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:02,458
is drying up rapidly
in this state.

29
00:01:02,541 --> 00:01:04,500
So the scabbard's not reacting
as it should.

30
00:01:04,583 --> 00:01:06,250
[LA HIRE]
Like in a children's story.

31
00:01:06,333 --> 00:01:09,416
The cursed princess will awaken
with the prince's kiss.

32
00:01:10,666 --> 00:01:12,625
[JEANNE moaning softly]

33
00:01:13,625 --> 00:01:15,208
[JEANNE weakly]
Montmorency.

34
00:01:16,500 --> 00:01:18,833
[sobbing]

35
00:01:18,916 --> 00:01:20,666
♪

36
00:03:00,500 --> 00:03:02,583
[SOLDIERS groaning]

37
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:10,375
[groans]
It's all over.

38
00:03:10,458 --> 00:03:11,708
France...

39
00:03:11,791 --> 00:03:12,958
France will fall.

40
00:03:13,041 --> 00:03:16,083
[JEANNE]
We're not finished!

41
00:03:16,166 --> 00:03:18,083
Don't give up yet!

42
00:03:18,166 --> 00:03:20,083
France endures!

43
00:03:20,166 --> 00:03:23,041
We will defeat the English.

44
00:03:23,125 --> 00:03:26,416
Countrymen, my full strength
is recovered.

45
00:03:27,875 --> 00:03:30,083
The Maiden of Domremy
fights for you.

46
00:03:30,166 --> 00:03:33,875
And I promise that I won't die
until I lead France to victory!

47
00:03:34,958 --> 00:03:39,458
Let us win this battle together
and take the Tourelles complex!

48
00:03:39,541 --> 00:03:42,208
[SOLDIERS cheering]

49
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:48,208
[GLASDALE]
Hmm.

50
00:03:48,291 --> 00:03:50,541
They're acting as though
Jesus Christ himself

51
00:03:50,625 --> 00:03:52,291
has been resurrected.

52
00:03:52,375 --> 00:03:55,166
But they'll find
that she's no savior.

53
00:03:55,250 --> 00:03:57,875
Montmorency must have discovered
some sort of magic

54
00:03:57,958 --> 00:03:59,583
that allowed her
to be healed.

55
00:03:59,666 --> 00:04:00,916
[scoffs]

56
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,666
If only you'd managed
to destroy her head

57
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:04,958
as we originally planned.

58
00:04:05,041 --> 00:04:06,750
[GLASDALE]
You would have fallen with her.

59
00:04:08,041 --> 00:04:09,875
Then you should have
killed me as well.

60
00:04:14,041 --> 00:04:16,625
Do not hesitate
next time, Glasdale.

61
00:04:16,708 --> 00:04:18,208
Strike her head.

62
00:04:29,500 --> 00:04:31,416
Hmm. I wonder.

63
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:33,625
Do you know the story
of a certain archer?

64
00:04:34,833 --> 00:04:35,916
He was an egotist

65
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:38,291
always boasting
about his skills,

66
00:04:38,375 --> 00:04:41,166
which brought him unwanted
attention from a feudal lord.

67
00:04:42,833 --> 00:04:44,416
He should have been
more than capable

68
00:04:44,500 --> 00:04:47,208
of shooting an apple
off his wife's head safely.

69
00:04:47,291 --> 00:04:49,291
That's the amount
of precision and control

70
00:04:49,375 --> 00:04:51,000
with which he aimed his bow.

71
00:04:52,083 --> 00:04:53,166
However...

72
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:56,333
[arrow looses]

73
00:04:59,916 --> 00:05:01,416
I do not fear death.

74
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:03,625
Don't let that worry
hold you back.

75
00:05:03,708 --> 00:05:06,916
In fact, I look forward
to the afterlife.

76
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:11,000
Death is a welcomed salvation
for a cursed Ulysses.

77
00:05:11,083 --> 00:05:12,916
It would bring me peace.

78
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:15,125
[door opens, closes]

79
00:05:15,208 --> 00:05:16,041
[GLASDALE]
Hmm.

80
00:05:23,541 --> 00:05:25,916
♪

81
00:05:28,583 --> 00:05:31,291
So you wish to die.

82
00:05:31,375 --> 00:05:33,041
[PHILIP]
I've been facing my mortality

83
00:05:33,125 --> 00:05:35,500
since the moment I first
put on the Holy Grail.

84
00:05:37,250 --> 00:05:40,083
I hoped it would reject me
and end my life.

85
00:05:41,083 --> 00:05:42,500
Unfortunately...

86
00:05:44,291 --> 00:05:48,291
Montmorency's elixir turned me
into Ulysses Noire instead.

87
00:05:51,291 --> 00:05:52,875
[JOHN]
It is your destiny to become

88
00:05:52,958 --> 00:05:55,208
the one true empress
of this world

89
00:05:55,291 --> 00:05:58,208
that is so full of
false kings and queens.

90
00:05:58,291 --> 00:06:01,416
You are not allowed to dream
of death until you rule.

91
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:03,041
That is your destiny.

92
00:06:05,208 --> 00:06:08,166
♪

93
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:11,041
Montmorency.

94
00:06:17,041 --> 00:06:20,083
The residents of Orleans
are rising up.

95
00:06:20,166 --> 00:06:23,041
They plan to open the gate,
cross the Loire River

96
00:06:23,125 --> 00:06:24,750
with a small group of ships

97
00:06:24,833 --> 00:06:28,041
and build a bridge
to the Tourelles complex.

98
00:06:28,125 --> 00:06:30,041
[BATARD] With our soldiers
at Augustine's fortress,


99
00:06:30,125 --> 00:06:32,500
we can attack the enemy
from both sides.


100
00:06:32,583 --> 00:06:33,833
[RICHEMONT] And what are
the movements

101
00:06:33,916 --> 00:06:35,208
of the English army?

102
00:06:35,291 --> 00:06:37,416
[ALENCON] They're gathering
at the complex.

103
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:40,333
Most likely to deal
with the citizens first.

104
00:06:40,416 --> 00:06:42,791
I'll rush to their aid
immediately.

105
00:06:42,875 --> 00:06:44,625
[MONTMORENCY]
No, you have to remain here.

106
00:06:44,708 --> 00:06:46,291
[gasps]

107
00:06:46,375 --> 00:06:49,333
[MONTMORENCY] We didn't heal you
just so you could die again.

108
00:06:49,416 --> 00:06:51,125
You want me cheer
our soldiers on

109
00:06:51,208 --> 00:06:52,750
from behind these walls?

110
00:06:52,833 --> 00:06:54,708
Why can't I help them?

111
00:06:54,791 --> 00:06:57,958
A Ulysses may draw upon
a single Philosopher's Stone.

112
00:06:58,041 --> 00:06:59,666
You remember.

113
00:06:59,750 --> 00:07:00,958
That's the rule.

114
00:07:02,208 --> 00:07:04,625
[thumping]

115
00:07:04,708 --> 00:07:06,166
You were able to absorb

116
00:07:06,250 --> 00:07:08,875
the power of
Excalibur's scabbard just once.

117
00:07:08,958 --> 00:07:11,333
Because you have
only half a stone.

118
00:07:11,416 --> 00:07:12,958
But it won't work again.

119
00:07:13,041 --> 00:07:15,375
The scabbard is useless
to you now.

120
00:07:15,458 --> 00:07:18,166
Which means if you fall
once more, we can't revive you.

121
00:07:18,250 --> 00:07:20,041
All it would take
is another well-aimed shot

122
00:07:20,125 --> 00:07:21,750
from Glasdale's bow.

123
00:07:21,833 --> 00:07:23,083
[gasps]

124
00:07:24,333 --> 00:07:26,208
There's no way
we can let that happen.

125
00:07:26,291 --> 00:07:27,791
How could we face
Princess Charlotte

126
00:07:27,875 --> 00:07:29,208
with news of your death?

127
00:07:29,291 --> 00:07:31,791
You can leave this fight to me
and Xaintrailles.

128
00:07:31,875 --> 00:07:35,375
Plus, don't forget that we have
2,000 reinforcement soldiers.

129
00:07:35,458 --> 00:07:36,375
[gasps]

130
00:07:36,458 --> 00:07:38,166
The Gilles de Rais squadron.

131
00:07:38,250 --> 00:07:39,875
Montmorency brought them here
from his home

132
00:07:39,958 --> 00:07:41,625
to help bolster our ranks.

133
00:07:41,708 --> 00:07:42,666
[JEANNE gasps]

134
00:07:42,750 --> 00:07:43,791
[MONTMORENCY]
Hmm.

135
00:07:45,458 --> 00:07:48,000
Ulysses Noire
has taken the bridge!

136
00:07:48,083 --> 00:07:49,583
[ALL gasp]

137
00:07:49,666 --> 00:07:51,583
-[screaming]
-[yelling]

138
00:07:54,333 --> 00:07:55,750
[ULYSSES NOIRE grunts]

139
00:07:55,833 --> 00:07:58,291
♪

140
00:08:01,291 --> 00:08:03,958
[laughing]

141
00:08:04,041 --> 00:08:06,083
Now I understand bloodlust.

142
00:08:07,291 --> 00:08:10,375
This crimson spray
is filling me with desire.

143
00:08:10,458 --> 00:08:11,750
[laughs]

144
00:08:13,500 --> 00:08:15,791
-[SOLDIERS screaming]
-[explosions]

145
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:24,500
♪

146
00:08:24,583 --> 00:08:26,000
[ALL gasp]

147
00:08:26,083 --> 00:08:27,375
What are you doing?

148
00:08:27,458 --> 00:08:30,333
Forgive me, but I'm arrogant
when I'm Ulysses.

149
00:08:36,791 --> 00:08:37,875
[scoffs]

150
00:08:37,958 --> 00:08:39,041
All right.

151
00:08:39,125 --> 00:08:40,625
Let's get on with it, you fools!

152
00:08:40,708 --> 00:08:41,791
[grunts]

153
00:08:41,875 --> 00:08:43,416
[GLASDALE]
Prepare to commence

154
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:45,500
Anti-Jeanne Operation
Number Two.

155
00:08:45,583 --> 00:08:47,791
[bowstrings tightening]

156
00:08:47,875 --> 00:08:49,125
[GLASDALE]
All units,

157
00:08:49,208 --> 00:08:51,250
your target will be
above the bridge.

158
00:08:51,333 --> 00:08:53,791
Noire will lure Jeanne
into your aim.

159
00:08:53,875 --> 00:08:56,125
Damn it. [grunts]

160
00:08:56,208 --> 00:08:58,041
Uh, where are you going?

161
00:08:58,125 --> 00:08:59,625
[grunts]

162
00:08:59,708 --> 00:09:01,375
♪

163
00:09:03,041 --> 00:09:04,458
[SOLDIERS grunting]

164
00:09:13,916 --> 00:09:15,333
[GLASDALE]
Don't bother shooting yet.

165
00:09:15,416 --> 00:09:16,625
She's too fast.

166
00:09:17,791 --> 00:09:19,750
If I can put this Ulysses down,

167
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:22,666
those weak French bastards
will become cowards once again.

168
00:09:22,750 --> 00:09:24,458
♪

169
00:09:24,541 --> 00:09:25,958
Huh?

170
00:09:26,041 --> 00:09:28,833
[laughing]

171
00:09:31,208 --> 00:09:32,500
-[JEANNE] Noire!
-[ULYSSES NOIRE gasps]

172
00:09:37,041 --> 00:09:38,250
[SOLDIER 1]
It's the maiden!

173
00:09:38,333 --> 00:09:40,083
[SOLDIER 2 sighs]
We're saved.

174
00:09:41,458 --> 00:09:44,083
[groans] We'll help you fight
however we can.

175
00:09:44,166 --> 00:09:45,916
Stay out of this.

176
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:47,416
[SOLDIER]
But...

177
00:09:47,500 --> 00:09:50,583
All I need right now
is your confidence.

178
00:09:50,666 --> 00:09:52,583
It's that faith that drives me.

179
00:09:52,666 --> 00:09:54,375
What keeps me fighting this war.

180
00:09:55,916 --> 00:09:57,000
[gasps]

181
00:09:58,375 --> 00:09:59,375
[chuckles]

182
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:02,916
[horse neighing]

183
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:03,916
[ASTAROTH]
Stop!

184
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,125
You've no hope of getting past

185
00:10:05,208 --> 00:10:06,875
the Tourelles complex
on your own.

186
00:10:06,958 --> 00:10:08,833
How can you be such a fool?

187
00:10:08,916 --> 00:10:10,541
[footsteps running]

188
00:10:10,625 --> 00:10:11,750
[ALENCON]
Montmorency!

189
00:10:11,833 --> 00:10:13,000
[MONTMORENCY]
Huh?

190
00:10:13,083 --> 00:10:15,041
Why are you rushing off
all by yourself?

191
00:10:16,791 --> 00:10:18,250
Have you forgotten?

192
00:10:18,333 --> 00:10:20,291
You have comrades with you.

193
00:10:20,375 --> 00:10:21,666
[BATARD]
That's right.

194
00:10:21,750 --> 00:10:24,791
We're willing to risk our lives,
by your side.

195
00:10:26,125 --> 00:10:27,541
Are you even listening?

196
00:10:29,250 --> 00:10:30,291
[MONTMORENCY sighs]

197
00:10:33,958 --> 00:10:37,000
[MONTMORENCY] I have no right
to ask for your aid.

198
00:10:37,083 --> 00:10:38,625
I'm not a warrior or saint

199
00:10:38,708 --> 00:10:41,416
who deserves to be rallied
behind in the name of France.

200
00:10:42,541 --> 00:10:44,208
In fact, I fight only to keep

201
00:10:44,291 --> 00:10:46,375
a long-held promise
to my friends.

202
00:10:48,083 --> 00:10:50,083
Until a few days ago,

203
00:10:50,166 --> 00:10:53,125
I didn't know what it meant
to care for someone.

204
00:10:53,208 --> 00:10:56,041
That's how much
I had yet to learn.

205
00:10:56,125 --> 00:10:58,750
But there's something
I can ask of you on this day.

206
00:10:59,750 --> 00:11:02,750
I beg you, lend me your strength
to protect the woman I love!

207
00:11:02,833 --> 00:11:04,416
[SOLDIERS cheering]

208
00:11:04,500 --> 00:11:06,208
♪

209
00:11:15,083 --> 00:11:16,750
Sir, they're attacking!

210
00:11:16,833 --> 00:11:17,666
[GLASDALE scoffs]

211
00:11:17,750 --> 00:11:20,041
♪

212
00:11:22,708 --> 00:11:24,250
[yelling]

213
00:11:27,583 --> 00:11:29,791
We're coming, Jeanne!

214
00:11:29,875 --> 00:11:31,791
Montmorency will protect you!

215
00:11:33,125 --> 00:11:35,958
What's with these peasants?
When did they get so strong?!

216
00:11:36,041 --> 00:11:37,333
Please, no!

217
00:11:37,416 --> 00:11:39,458
I do not want to die
in this wretched country.

218
00:11:39,541 --> 00:11:42,958
[MAN] I'll gladly spill my blood
for France!

219
00:11:43,041 --> 00:11:44,750
[neighing]

220
00:11:46,875 --> 00:11:48,625
Hurry, Montmorency.

221
00:11:48,708 --> 00:11:50,458
We'll be able to
hold them off here.

222
00:11:50,541 --> 00:11:52,541
Well, what the hell
are you waiting for?

223
00:11:52,625 --> 00:11:53,500
[gunshot]

224
00:11:53,583 --> 00:11:54,750
[MONTMORENCY]
All right.

225
00:11:56,333 --> 00:11:57,750
[MONTMORENCY]
Almost there, Jeanne.

226
00:11:57,833 --> 00:11:59,416
I won't let you fight alone.

227
00:12:00,791 --> 00:12:04,416
I will be right beside you,
until the bitter end!

228
00:12:06,166 --> 00:12:07,666
[yelling]

229
00:12:07,750 --> 00:12:10,458
♪

230
00:12:15,250 --> 00:12:16,125
[JEANNE]
Too slow.

231
00:12:16,208 --> 00:12:17,791
[BOTH grunt]

232
00:12:17,875 --> 00:12:19,041
[ULYSSES NOIRE screams]

233
00:12:21,333 --> 00:12:24,125
Cut me all you like. I'll live.

234
00:12:26,375 --> 00:12:28,250
This helmet is the Holy Grail.

235
00:12:28,333 --> 00:12:30,500
It possesses
the ultimate healing power.

236
00:12:31,750 --> 00:12:33,458
You cannot kill me.

237
00:12:34,916 --> 00:12:37,125
[scoffs] Then next time
I'll crush your helmet

238
00:12:37,208 --> 00:12:38,708
along with your head.

239
00:12:38,791 --> 00:12:40,041
[SOLDIER]
Be on your guard!

240
00:12:40,125 --> 00:12:42,041
They're aiming at you
from the complex.

241
00:12:42,125 --> 00:12:43,250
I am well aware.

242
00:12:43,333 --> 00:12:46,708
♪

243
00:12:46,791 --> 00:12:49,333
[JEANNE] The only thing to fear
is the Holy Lance Arrow.

244
00:12:50,583 --> 00:12:54,041
But Glasdale can't keep up
with my acceleration.

245
00:12:54,125 --> 00:12:56,041
And neither can she.

246
00:12:56,125 --> 00:12:57,666
I'll win this fight.

247
00:12:58,791 --> 00:13:00,875
[ULYSSES NOIRE]
The Gilles de Rais squadron.

248
00:13:00,958 --> 00:13:02,166
[JEANNE gasps]

249
00:13:02,250 --> 00:13:04,250
I wonder what Montmorency
had to do

250
00:13:04,333 --> 00:13:07,416
to obtain 2,000 reinforcements
from his grandfather.

251
00:13:07,500 --> 00:13:09,125
[gasps]

252
00:13:09,208 --> 00:13:10,708
[ULYSSES NOIRE laughs]

253
00:13:10,791 --> 00:13:13,166
You really don't understand yet?

254
00:13:13,250 --> 00:13:14,208
[chuckles]

255
00:13:16,500 --> 00:13:17,958
[yelling]

256
00:13:19,875 --> 00:13:21,375
[gasps]

257
00:13:23,666 --> 00:13:24,916
[MONTMORENCY]
Jeanne!

258
00:13:33,666 --> 00:13:35,125
[ULYSSES NOIRE]
Montmorency received

259
00:13:35,208 --> 00:13:38,625
his army and family fortune
from Jean the Redbeard.

260
00:13:38,708 --> 00:13:41,416
But that man
is not a kind person.

261
00:13:41,500 --> 00:13:43,791
Montmorency must have
pleased him.

262
00:13:43,875 --> 00:13:47,291
Likely by marrying
his cousin, Catherine.

263
00:13:47,375 --> 00:13:49,083
[JEANNE groans softly]

264
00:13:49,166 --> 00:13:50,958
[MONTMORENCY panting]
There you are!

265
00:13:51,041 --> 00:13:52,083
Are you all right?

266
00:13:53,333 --> 00:13:54,375
Jeanne?

267
00:13:55,375 --> 00:13:57,666
[JEANNE]
Did you break your promise?

268
00:13:57,750 --> 00:14:00,625
You said that you and I
would be together forever.

269
00:14:00,708 --> 00:14:02,125
That you would never marry
someone else

270
00:14:02,208 --> 00:14:03,416
and leave me behind.

271
00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:04,416
[MONTMORENCY gasps]

272
00:14:04,500 --> 00:14:06,000
How tragic.

273
00:14:06,083 --> 00:14:08,208
Your little heart is broken.

274
00:14:08,291 --> 00:14:11,666
Montmorency,
exactly what am I to you?

275
00:14:11,750 --> 00:14:15,000
Nothing more than a weapon
to use against the English?

276
00:14:15,083 --> 00:14:17,208
[MONTMORENCY]
Of course that's not the case.

277
00:14:17,291 --> 00:14:19,041
But I had no other choice.

278
00:14:19,125 --> 00:14:20,916
Catherine is like
a sister to me.

279
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:22,458
[cries softly]

280
00:14:22,541 --> 00:14:24,000
[gasps]

281
00:14:24,083 --> 00:14:25,375
[ULYSSES NOIRE chuckles]

282
00:14:26,916 --> 00:14:27,958
[MONTMORENCY]
Jeanne!

283
00:14:28,041 --> 00:14:31,333
Do not interrupt us, Noire!

284
00:14:31,416 --> 00:14:32,458
[gasps]

285
00:14:32,541 --> 00:14:33,958
Stupid little girl.

286
00:14:34,041 --> 00:14:36,000
You allowed yourself
to be provoked into an attack

287
00:14:36,083 --> 00:14:37,583
that you knew would fail.

288
00:14:37,666 --> 00:14:38,916
You're open.

289
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:40,041
[JEANNE groans]

290
00:14:41,291 --> 00:14:42,458
Jeanne, no!

291
00:14:42,541 --> 00:14:44,083
[GLASDALE]
Now's our chance. Take aim!

292
00:14:45,083 --> 00:14:46,166
[MONTMORENCY]
Archers.

293
00:14:47,208 --> 00:14:49,375
♪

294
00:14:51,458 --> 00:14:53,708
[ASTAROTH]
Wait! What are you doing?

295
00:14:53,791 --> 00:14:54,791
Montmorency!

296
00:14:57,166 --> 00:14:58,375
[GLASDALE]
Fire at will!

297
00:14:58,458 --> 00:15:00,208
[arrows releasing]

298
00:15:02,166 --> 00:15:03,166
[JEANNE gasps]
No.

299
00:15:05,166 --> 00:15:07,000
[ULYSSES NOIRE]
Only one is lethal.

300
00:15:07,083 --> 00:15:08,875
But how will you find it?

301
00:15:08,958 --> 00:15:11,916
Especially when you can't
accelerate while in the air.

302
00:15:14,291 --> 00:15:16,291
Let us die here together,
Jeanne.

303
00:15:21,041 --> 00:15:22,083
[groans softly]

304
00:15:22,166 --> 00:15:23,041
[gasps]

305
00:15:25,916 --> 00:15:27,375
[breathes shakily]

306
00:15:30,708 --> 00:15:31,666
[sighs]

307
00:15:38,083 --> 00:15:39,750
[MONTMORENCY]
I swear,

308
00:15:39,833 --> 00:15:42,541
you're the most troublesome lady
in the world, do you know that?

309
00:15:42,625 --> 00:15:44,208
-Truly.
-[JEANNE gasps]

310
00:15:47,250 --> 00:15:48,583
Montmorency.

311
00:15:49,583 --> 00:15:51,708
When I swallowed the Stone,
I just knew.

312
00:15:56,500 --> 00:15:59,791
I have the other half
of the one that's inside of you.

313
00:15:59,875 --> 00:16:03,666
Your power is to attack,
and mine's to defend.

314
00:16:03,750 --> 00:16:05,208
Together, we're whole!

315
00:16:06,875 --> 00:16:07,916
No. It can't be.

316
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:10,333
♪

317
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:15,166
[MONTMORENCY] I can make the air
harder than steel.

318
00:16:16,208 --> 00:16:18,291
Think I'll call it Mur D'Air.

319
00:16:18,375 --> 00:16:20,541
Now the very air
I breathe protects you.

320
00:16:20,625 --> 00:16:23,041
You actually swallowed
the Philosopher's Stone?

321
00:16:23,125 --> 00:16:25,375
How can you be so stupid?

322
00:16:25,458 --> 00:16:27,166
[ASTAROTH gasps]

323
00:16:27,250 --> 00:16:28,583
[ASTAROTH] It's likely that you
can only withstand being Ulysses

324
00:16:28,666 --> 00:16:30,208
for three minutes at most.

325
00:16:30,291 --> 00:16:32,125
Your body will continue
to transmute elixir,

326
00:16:32,208 --> 00:16:33,750
which will react with the Stone,

327
00:16:33,833 --> 00:16:35,958
causing it to become unstable
and spiral out of control.

328
00:16:36,041 --> 00:16:37,583
You may die of madness

329
00:16:37,666 --> 00:16:39,541
as soon as the Stone
takes over your mind,

330
00:16:39,625 --> 00:16:41,916
or perhaps
you might simply explode.

331
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:43,333
Whatever the case may be,

332
00:16:43,416 --> 00:16:45,375
the consequences range
from bad to catastrophic.

333
00:16:45,458 --> 00:16:46,916
[JEANNE groans]

334
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,625
[JEANNE] I'll have to rip
the Stone from your stomach.

335
00:16:48,708 --> 00:16:51,000
[MONTMORENCY] That's insane.
Are you wanting to kill me?

336
00:16:51,083 --> 00:16:52,458
Jeanne!

337
00:16:52,541 --> 00:16:54,916
♪

338
00:16:56,041 --> 00:16:58,000
I managed to harden the air
around her feet.

339
00:16:58,083 --> 00:16:59,500
Now's your chance!

340
00:16:59,583 --> 00:17:01,333
I can't crush that helmet.

341
00:17:01,416 --> 00:17:02,375
[MONTMORENCY]
You have to try.

342
00:17:02,458 --> 00:17:04,166
We're both running out of time.

343
00:17:06,083 --> 00:17:07,166
Go, now!

344
00:17:09,041 --> 00:17:10,916
[JEANNE yelling]

345
00:17:12,583 --> 00:17:13,875
[groans]

346
00:17:13,958 --> 00:17:16,291
Don't you remember?
You already tried that.

347
00:17:17,375 --> 00:17:18,791
Take the shot!

348
00:17:21,083 --> 00:17:22,375
Ashes to ashes.

349
00:17:22,458 --> 00:17:24,041
It's time to end this.

350
00:17:24,125 --> 00:17:26,375
Glasdale, do not hesitate.

351
00:17:26,458 --> 00:17:27,916
Strike us down.

352
00:17:29,458 --> 00:17:30,583
[sighs]

353
00:17:31,708 --> 00:17:33,166
♪

354
00:17:33,250 --> 00:17:34,541
[BOTH grunting]

355
00:17:34,625 --> 00:17:36,666
[MONTMORENCY]
I won't let you die.

356
00:17:36,750 --> 00:17:38,166
-[ULYSSES NOIRE grunts]
-[JEANNE groans]

357
00:17:38,250 --> 00:17:39,625
You idiot, now!

358
00:17:39,708 --> 00:17:41,333
History will remember you
as a failure

359
00:17:41,416 --> 00:17:42,541
if you don't shoot us!

360
00:17:42,625 --> 00:17:44,041
♪

361
00:17:44,125 --> 00:17:45,708
[grunting]

362
00:17:46,958 --> 00:17:48,041
[MONTMORENCY]
I won't allow it!

363
00:17:48,125 --> 00:17:49,208
[grunts]

364
00:17:56,291 --> 00:17:58,458
Break through, come on!

365
00:17:58,541 --> 00:18:00,166
[grunting]

366
00:18:03,708 --> 00:18:05,291
[groans sharply]

367
00:18:05,375 --> 00:18:06,250
[MONTMORENCY]
Oh, God!

368
00:18:10,791 --> 00:18:12,333
Jeanne, no!

369
00:18:12,416 --> 00:18:15,083
♪

370
00:18:16,208 --> 00:18:17,375
[ULYSSES NOIRE]
Glasdale.

371
00:18:19,416 --> 00:18:20,791
You hesitated.

372
00:18:23,416 --> 00:18:24,833
[ULYSSES NOIRE gasps]

373
00:18:24,916 --> 00:18:26,791
-[JEANNE grunts]
-[ULYSSES NOIRE screams]

374
00:18:28,458 --> 00:18:29,291
[groans]

375
00:18:32,291 --> 00:18:34,250
[ULYSSES NOIRE]
You have Montmorency's love.

376
00:18:35,541 --> 00:18:37,166
You hoarded it from me.

377
00:18:39,625 --> 00:18:40,791
[GLASDALE]
Noire!

378
00:18:40,875 --> 00:18:43,250
♪

379
00:18:50,875 --> 00:18:51,833
[GLASDALE grunts]

380
00:18:54,166 --> 00:18:55,291
[JEANNE gasps]

381
00:18:55,375 --> 00:18:56,458
[yells]

382
00:18:58,458 --> 00:18:59,791
Montmorency.

383
00:18:59,875 --> 00:19:00,875
[chuckles softly]

384
00:19:04,625 --> 00:19:05,666
[chuckles softly]

385
00:19:08,375 --> 00:19:09,750
[BOTH sigh]

386
00:19:11,041 --> 00:19:12,041
[MONTMORENCY groans]

387
00:19:15,875 --> 00:19:17,666
[MAN]
We won.

388
00:19:17,750 --> 00:19:20,083
The maiden is victorious!

389
00:19:20,166 --> 00:19:22,166
[ALL cheering]

390
00:19:31,916 --> 00:19:33,500
[cheering continues]

391
00:19:36,625 --> 00:19:39,375
[ASTAROTH] Montmorency,
is your body surviving?

392
00:19:39,458 --> 00:19:40,541
[MONTMORENCY]
Yeah.

393
00:19:40,625 --> 00:19:42,458
I felt strange there
for a second,

394
00:19:42,541 --> 00:19:44,250
but I'm fine.

395
00:19:45,375 --> 00:19:46,958
[ASTAROTH gasps]

396
00:19:47,041 --> 00:19:49,333
I guess your prediction about
something terrible happening

397
00:19:49,416 --> 00:19:51,041
wasn't very reliable,

398
00:19:51,125 --> 00:19:53,541
which means I probably should've
been Ulysses this entire time

399
00:19:53,625 --> 00:19:55,000
and saved Jeanne
a lot of trouble.

400
00:19:55,083 --> 00:19:56,541
-[heartbeat]
-[MONTMORENCY gasps]

401
00:19:57,541 --> 00:19:59,333
What is it?

402
00:19:59,416 --> 00:20:02,000
[MONTMORENCY strained]
Nothing. I don't think...

403
00:20:02,083 --> 00:20:03,375
[MONTMORENCY groans]

404
00:20:03,458 --> 00:20:06,166
♪

405
00:20:13,375 --> 00:20:15,166
[SOLDIERS gasp]

406
00:20:17,500 --> 00:20:20,458
Are you serious?
What's going on now?

407
00:20:20,541 --> 00:20:21,875
Could this be
the English casting

408
00:20:21,958 --> 00:20:23,875
some sort of magic spell?

409
00:20:23,958 --> 00:20:25,833
No, it's not.

410
00:20:26,916 --> 00:20:31,291
This force is something
far more terrible.

411
00:20:31,375 --> 00:20:33,791
[thunder rumbling]

412
00:20:33,875 --> 00:20:36,333
♪

413
00:20:38,041 --> 00:20:40,250
[NICOLAS]
Who would've thought that love,

414
00:20:40,333 --> 00:20:42,958
a single, pure act of devotion,

415
00:20:43,041 --> 00:20:45,250
would trigger
the end of the world.

416
00:20:48,708 --> 00:20:51,208
The fifth dimension's unfolding

417
00:20:51,291 --> 00:20:54,666
alongside the sixth one
and the seventh.

418
00:20:54,750 --> 00:20:55,958
They're all...

419
00:20:57,041 --> 00:20:57,875
[gasps]

420
00:20:57,958 --> 00:21:00,500
No. It can't be.

421
00:21:00,583 --> 00:21:01,875
This is the end.

422
00:21:01,958 --> 00:21:03,083
We're doomed.

423
00:21:03,166 --> 00:21:06,125
♪

424
00:21:09,666 --> 00:21:12,875
This is something
I never thought I'd see.

425
00:21:12,958 --> 00:21:15,333
The Philosopher's Stone
will kill us all.

426
00:21:15,416 --> 00:21:16,833
Wait, hold on.

427
00:21:16,916 --> 00:21:18,625
I thought you said
I was just going to die

428
00:21:18,708 --> 00:21:20,333
if I went out of control.

429
00:21:20,416 --> 00:21:21,666
What is that thing?

430
00:23:27,750 --> 00:23:29,208
[NARRATOR] I heard
from the English soldiers

431
00:23:29,291 --> 00:23:30,958
that breasts are called
"boobs" in their country.

432
00:23:31,041 --> 00:23:32,291
It is a fitting word,

433
00:23:32,375 --> 00:23:33,541
considering it looks like
what it refers to.

434
00:23:33,625 --> 00:23:35,458
What voluptuous Bs and Os.

435
00:23:35,541 --> 00:23:37,875
Episode 10,
"Beast of the Apocalypse."

436
00:23:37,958 --> 00:23:39,791
Isn't it fun to expand
your vocabulary?

437
00:23:39,875 --> 00:23:41,916
Who needs school
when you have me?

438
00:23:44,041 --> 00:23:44,916
[WOMAN]
Repliez-vous.

